caption: Recently ordered delivery from this JJ location on Euclid. It is only 0.2 miles from my location. JJ’s are known for their fast delivery. My sandwich took approx an hour and 1/2 to arrive. I contacted store location after an hour of waiting and young woman said driver had 4 other deliveries along with mine on his outing and that he should arrive shortly?? Driver never notified me or knocked on door as per instructions to let me know my order had arrived; I just happened to check after an hour and a half. The sandwich looked a bit disheveled. Also, the day before I placed an order on the website for delivery approx. 10 minutes prior to the store closing. I was phoned by the store advising me they could not honor my order because they had closed everything up. I was charged for sandwich and I am still awaiting a refund to my card. I would recommend some sort of cutoff time when ordering from the website prior to store closing or redirecting you to the closest location for delivery.
They are the slowest ever.
Clearly 1 manager is more neighborly and friendly than the other... hope you get the more welcoming!
Fast delivery, Awesome food, Great staff! What more could you ask for than a 5 star service for less than $20.delivered...

I visited the Jimmy John’s restaurant at 13 North Euclid in St. Louis, Missouri 63108 on December 5, 2020. I am a regular customer since I live just 1-1/2 blocks away. While there eating my sandwich, I noticed the 2 employees standing face-to-face talking about 3 feet apart not wearing masks. I pointed out to them the necessity of wearing masks and socially distancing and they informed me that they did not have to since they were working there together. I share with them that over 250,000 Americans have died from Covid. Those facts did not matter to them. I took a photo and a couple videos documenting the situation and they became loud and belligerent toward me. They told me that I have been banned from their location, and called the police to have me arrested for trespassing. When the police arrived, I promptly left the store, but also explained the situation to them. My next step is to report this location to the St. Louis Health Department and ask that this location’s license be suspended.
Went in today (Nov 30) for lunch. GM's mask was off and she was coughing before and after she made my sandwich. Had to throw it out.

Pleasant experience! Would be 5 stars except we asked for peppers added to one sandwich and it didn't have peppers but that could have been due to confusion about another topping I asked about. Sandwiches were delicious and delivery was friendly and truly freaky fast (despite my calling the hotel by an old name)!

The lady was talking on her personal cellphone with ear piece the whole 20 minutes I was in there. I placed online order for pickup at 1135 am. I walked in at 1141 am went to the pickup counter. She waited on a group of people that walked in. I asked her if she had my order and she snap at me, "Have not talked to you" then she finished  all the walk up orders first and then my order. I walked out of there after 12pm. Get home and my order was not correct. Not a happy customer.
despite thorough and detailed delivery instructions, they are never follow and I never receive a call to inform me that they aren't being followed
The hunters club is great

You would think that there is nothing more simple and straightforward than a sandwich shop but the people here make it seem like rocket science.  When I asked for meat, cheese, and bread, they looked at me like I had two heads.  I settled for one of their menu items with a few modifications and received a meager portion to boot!

TLDR: I would give this 0 stars if possible.  Took close to an hour and a half for 1 sandwich to be delivered.  I live close to 3 blocks away.  Should have just walked and got it myself.  Ordered a sandwich at a slower time of day.  After 40 minutes of not getting the sandwich and then receiving notification that it had been delivered, I called the store,  the employees forgot to place me on hold and instead argued about whose responsibility it was to deliver the sandwich/ make sure it was delivered.  Employee came back and said they had a misunderstanding and that it was "walking out the door right now"  40 more minutes go by, I call again, the employee says the person delivering my sandwich had their bike break when they were part way to me, so they had to come back and get a new bike.  I live 3 blocks away....... their line of thinking was to get nearly halfway to me, turn around and prolong this already absurdly long delivery.  Great work
Horribly rude and inconsiderate. They made the sandwich and said nothing
Rude, terrible customer service don’t go there Has flies, mold on Sandwhiches bread did not use gloves while making my sandwich and the smell was horrible. Won’t be going back!!!

I wish I could attach a picture in here. But I am trying to enjoy my sandwich and then I see a hair. I have red hair not black hair. That’s really gross. That’s is why you should keep your hair put up. It’s just so gross. If you would like to see the picture go to yelp to see the review.
Great Place, quick Delivery and the best MGMT. I order bulk lunch deliveries for meetings across the street at BJC and they are always delivered on time and fresh.
Don't go here worst Jimmy John's in St. Louis, you will be waiting for hours for your food, then I didn't get all my order, stay away, I warned you
Super fast and courteous. Handled my big order with ease.

So fast. It takes me longer to figure out what I want than it does for them to make my sandwich. There is hardly ever a wait for dinner here. The ingredients were very fresh. They should have a bacon tuna combo on their menu though. The giant sandwich is huge. I saved the other half of it for a 2nd meal for late at night.
This place used to keep the fast service motto of the chain. The  last 3 times I've ordered, I've ended up calling asking where my order is? Time for a new sandwich place
Prices high customer service is great but damn  the prices for a sandwich that  u can make at home
The delivery driver is a rude moron. Went to the wrong address and then got an attitude and hung up on me when I called.

I found that the staff was friendly and the location was clean, which was nice upon entry. I found that food was cooked as expected, the building was clean, and the restrooms were clean as well. I had no complaints about my experience in this particular location. Thanks and keep up the good work.
Great food great staff
SUPER SLOW DELIVERY Service.   30 min at least for one sandwich and I am less than two miles away.

I order lunch online around 10:15am Friday August 17th I didn't realize until after I confirmed my order that it said delivery asap, so I called the store and spoke to someone and ask them if they could deliver my order at 12 noon and he said ok and he took my name because my order to come through on there end yet. I didn't receive my lunch until 12:25 which means I either going have to eat my lunch real fast or take a few bites before I go back to work or just not eat my lunch at all! I have ordered lunch from here before without ever a issue and I know they come on bikes so this last order which was today I gave a little more on the tip side which nobody deserved. I did call and spoke to someone before my food showed up and told them that I wasn't happy I didn't go off or act crazy I was cool about it they apologized so I ask to talk to the manager but he was busy so they said they would have him or she call me back, never received that call. I work for a construction company and we do work all over the city I'm also a Union member, I will be letting people know about this Jimmy John's and I probably won't be eating Jimmy John's anymore no matter how much I like it especially since the manager didn't return my call customer appreciation goes a long way. I probably wouldn't have a issue or be writing this if I did receive a call. 0 stars is my review! God bless.

Worst jimmy johns ever. I ordered and before worker even left jimmy johns called to tell me that security would not let them bring it up. After I got all unhooked and went downstairs to get food, security told me they let him up. Sandwich bread tasted like Day old bread times 20. Soda 30 oz was flat and terrible. I love jimmy johns soda and order every time so I don’t know what happened to this jimmy johns, it is unbelievably terrible, and this is coming from a starved patient who hasn’t eaten in two days!

Ordered a Vito Italian sandwich with some extra lettuce and turkey.  12.65 sandwich arrived.  I paid, tipped, and returned to my desk.  The sandwich  had lettuce, cucumber, and turkey.  No vito meat, no dressing,  no tomato.  I called, they offered a credit on my next sandwich.  I won't be ordering another.  Thank you.
Great delivery service! Even better food!
On multiple occasions I've ordered online, arrived 10-15 minutes later to find out they haven't even started on my sandwich. They have an alternate definition of "as soon as possible."
What a joke.
Not freaky fast. Old ingredients. Smoking weed in the back instead of helping customers. And rushed paying customers out. Bad Jimmy John's.
Disappointed

Received my food an hour and a half late. Called twice and was pretty much given excuses as to why it was late (the rain, only two drivers, etc.) I understand you are busy and short staffed, but an automated system should be in place if your order is delayed. I received no apologies. Won't be utilizing this location anymore. Shame they've lost out on a ton of catering orders.
Great subs!

Kat (the GM) provides horrible customer service.  My online order was placed over 1.5 hours ago and I have still not received my sandwich.   Naturally, I call to check the status of the order because I did receive a text notification that the amount has been taken out of my account from Jimmy Johns of $11.50.  Apparently they never received my order because there was an issue with the online website.  They suggest I contact their corporate office to resolve at $11.50 issue.  What a joke.  No compensation, no apology, horrible customer service.  I'm very disappointment with my experience here and guarantee my business will be taken elsewhere.
Sandwiches are delicous, service and delivery are both very fast.
Quick service, very friendly
Ordered over the phone, and have been waiting over 2 hours for my food. Terrible service
We had the beach club. It was light and refreshing. Parking can be hard to find here. Street only.
Great location!
AWFUL!! Took an hour and 15 min to get my sandwich and I had to order it twice because they wrote my phone number AND credit card # down wrong. Absolutely ridiculous.
The sandwich was ok. This particular location was clean and service was quick.
Friendly staff and quick service
The sandwiches always taste good, and are usually built well. Sometimes they fall apart.
Truly bizarre experience. Ordered a sandwich at 11:52; still not here at 12:52. Called three times and it just rings. Thank goodness I paid (and tipped) in advance. #justplainfreaky
Picklemans Really Have Them Beat. JJ's Dont Deliever To Houses Thats Literally Less Than A Mile From Them.
They are indeed freaky fast while maintaining tasty sandwiches.

Over an hour for a delivery that Google quoted as "4 minutes away" Cups shoddily taped shut and covered with Saran Wrap. Soda inside completely flat and watered down by the ice that has melted for an hour. But at least when they finally brought us the food, they also didn't apologize or acknowledge that they took over an hour to bring us 2 sandwiches and drinks. We won't be ordering from them again. Unless you live less than 4 minutes away, order in advance. Way in advance.
An employee and I ate at this location last Friday, I had the bootlegger and she had the tuna salad... and we both got food poisoning... not the freaky fast we were looking for..

Great service always, and quick!  They deliver just as quick as if you ordered in store.  And delivery is open till middle of the night.  Which is always a positive in case you ever need something at odd hours delivered.
This Jimmy Johns (like most) is freaky fast. Customer service is good and the food is fresh
Honestly great service every time I order. Occasionally there's a slight delay, but the deliver folks are so kind and courteous I don't even mind! Great staff, great service, what more can I say?

Great service. The customer service is top notch, a level above the competetion. Everytime i walk in i am greeted with hello and promptly asked for my order. The staff is friendly and the food is fast and fresh. A great place to have lunch in a hurry!

This was the first time I have ever ordered from here. The employee that took my order was courteous. He gave a brief rundown of the menu, very helpful.  The food arrived within 8 mins (great), but someone forgot my drink. Which was on the receipt stapled to the bag, showing I ordered 1. Driver was courteous enough (no questions asked) to go back and return promptly with my drink. Overall good food, will see what happens the next time.
